2 argument, data, and views on the proposed turnpike to the Authority;
3 4. Consider the effect its intended action may have on the
4 various types of property owners, businesses, and governmental
5 entities. Except where such modification or variance is prohibited
6 by statutory or constitutional constraints, if the Authority finds
7 that its actions may adversely affect any such entity, the Authority
8 may modify its proposal. For business entities, the Authority shall
9 include a description of the probable quantitative and qualitative
10 impact of the proposed turnpike, economic or otherwise, and use
11 quantifiable data to the extent possible, considering both short-
12 term and long-term consequences;
13 5. Consider the effect its intended action may have on the
14 various types of consumer groups. If the Authority finds that its
15 actions may adversely affect such groups, the Authority may modify
16 its proposal to exclude the activity that may potentially cause such
17 adverse effects; and
18 6. When the Authority provides notice pursuant to paragraph 1
19 of this subsection, provide one electronic copy of the complete map
20 of the proposed turnpike to the Governor, the President Pro Tempore
21 of the Senate, and the Speaker of the House of Representatives.
22 B. The notice required by paragraph 1 of subsection A of this
23 section shall include, but not be limited to:
